ion.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40256.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>3, A <em>house</em> is not a home.&nbsp;<a href='/s/47804.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>4, Who repairs not his gutter repairs his whole <em>house</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42313.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>5, The <em>house</em> of every one is to him as his castle and fortress.&nbsp;<a href='/s/47182.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>6, It is a sad <em>house</em> where the hen crows louder than the cock.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41252.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>7, A <em>house</em> divided against itself cannot stand.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42443.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div id="ad_marginbottom_0" style="margin-top:-10px;margin-bottom:5px;"><script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script><!-- 728_90_20170421 --><ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:inline-block;width:728px;height:90px" data-ad-client="ca-pub-7200850114163593" data-ad-slot="2392632666"></ins><script>(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});</script></div><div>8, The wife is the key of the <em>house</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42096.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>9, A fool knows more in his own <em>house</em> than a wise man in another's.&nbsp;<a href='/s/193289.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>10, A man may love his <em>house</em> well without riding on the ridge.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40441.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>11, Hang up one's hat in another's <em>house</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42904.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>12, A fool knows more in his own <em>house</em> than a wise man in another.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42410.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>13, A man’s <em>house</em> is his castle.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40446.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>14, Burn not your <em>house</em> to rid it of the mouse.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42643.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>15, There is a skeleton in every <em>house</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42023.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>16, He who lives in glass <em>house</em> should not throw stones.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42998.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>17, As the <em>house</em> is to the man(sentencedict.com), so is the nest to the bird and the cave to the animal.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40521.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>18, Who holds the purse rules the <em>house</em>.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42302.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>19, Buying a <em>house</em> is the best hedge against inflation.</div><div>20, We've got a mouse in the <em>house</em>.</div><div>21, The burglar got into the <em>house</em> through the bedroom window.</div><div>22, He was left alone in the <em>house</em>.</div><div>23, The <em>house</em> is on the side of a hill.</div><div>24, The more women look in their glass,(http://sentencedict.com/<em>house</em>.html) the less they look to their house.&nbsp;<a href='/s/42000.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>25, Two cats and a mouse, two wives in one <em>house</em>, two dogs and a bone, never agree in one.&nbsp;<a href='/s/44072.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>26, By the street of “Bye-and-bye” one arrives at the <em>house</em> of “Never”.&nbsp;<a href='/s/40649.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>27, To marry a woman for her beauty is like buying a <em>house</em> for its paint.&nbsp;<a href='/s/44034.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>28, It is no good hen that cackles in your <em>house</em> and lays in another’s.&nbsp;<a href='/s/41286.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div>29, It is too late to come with the water when the <em>house</em> is burnt down.&nbsp;<a href='/s/43186.html' target='blank' title='into the page of the sentence'><img src='/images/enter.jpg' style='vertical-align:bottom'/></a></div><div style="margin-bottom:3px;">30, The decision was announced after objections were raised in the Upper <em>House</em> of Parliament.</div></div><!--all结束-->  <!--如果不是仅显示学生,或该页没有学生句子-->  <div id="student" style='display:none;'>  <div>1, We've got a mouse in the <em>house</em>.</div><div>2, The outer walls of the <em>house</em> were made of brick.</div><div>3, Who was the original owner of this <em>house</em>?</div><div>4, There was not a single person in the <em>house</em>.</div><div>5, My father accidentally locked me out of the <em>house</em>.</div><div>6, It's an awful nuisance having builders in the <em>house</em> all day.</div><div>7, It took all our savings to buy the <em>house</em>.</div><div>8, Mother went shopping; meanwhile, I cleaned the <em>house</em>.</div><div>9, The <em>house</em> went to rack and ruin.</div><div>10, The man walked into the <em>house</em> in the dark.</div><div>11, There is an underground room in the old <em>house</em>.</div><div>12, The foreign guests were motored to the guest <em>house</em>.</div><div>13, This <em>house</em> is my only property.</div><div>14, A warm <em>house</em> and good food are material comforts.</div><div>15, Give the <em>house</em> a thorough cleaning.</div><div>16, We rented a <em>house</em> on the seafront for the summer.</div><div>17, I'll be so jealous if you manage to wangle an invitation to his <em>house</em>.</div><div>18, Visiting her <em>house</em> was like stepping back in time/stepping back 50 years.</div><div>19, Please make sure that the <em>house</em> is locked before you leave.</div><div>20, Ann stopped in front of the <em>house</em>.</div><div>21, They're building an extension to their <em>house</em>.</div><div>22, The telephone wire is cut off in this <em>house</em>.</div><div>23, You must see the inside of a <em>house</em> before you buy it.</div><div>24, They finished the <em>house</em> within half a year.</div><div>25, The firefighter broke into the <em>house</em> to rescue the old.</div><div>26, He had met his old lady when he was a <em>house</em> painter and she was a waitress.</div><div>27, He